    "Section 6 demonstrates the experimental scenario results and discusses the main findings.",
    "Section 7 concludes and highlights particular future work directions.",
    "Background and Literature ReviewThe notion of an ontology, as defined by Gruber [23], refers to an \"explicit specification of a conceptualization.\"",
    "Subsequently, different definitions of ontology are presented, Borst [24] defined an ontology as a \"formal specification of a shared conceptualization\".",
    "Ontology is also defined as a \"knowledge domain conceptualization into a computer processable format, which axioms\" [25]."
